    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "PAN AMERICAN WORLD AIRWAYS SYSTEM\n28-19 Briage Plaza North\nLong Island City 1, N.Y.\nThere is (are) enclosed herewith the first flight cover(s) which\nyou forwarded on the recent inaugural air mail service between San\nFrancisco, California; Honolulu, I. H.; and Canton Island, to Sydney,\nAustralia, in care of our Agent at that point.\nWe trust you will find the cover(s) satisfactory.\nInquiries con-\ncerning the cover(s), if any should arise, should be addressed to the\nPostmaster to whom you forwarded the cover(s) for posting and not to\nthis Company. Our participation in this service was limited to return-\ning the cover(s) addressed in care of our Agent at Sydney to the senders\nupon completion of the flight.\nIt is our expectation that, in the near future, we will have for\nsale to all interested philatelists, first flight covers from Suva,\nFiji Islands, and Noumea, New Caledonia to Sydney, Australia. Also,\nfirst flight covers\nfrom Sydney, Australia to Noumea, Suva, Canton\nIsland, Honolulu and San Francisco, on the return trip. Up to this\ndate, however, the Australian Postal Service has not utilized the ser-\nvices of Pan American Airways, Inc. for the carriage of their mails to\nthe points indicated above, but it is expected that the service will be\nused in the very near future.\nIf your name is not on our philatelic list and you wish to receive\nthe announcement describing the above-mentioned first flight covers,\nplease advise us.\nPAN AMERICAN AIRMAYS, INC.\nPhilatelic Section"
